article.headline: Southern 70, Jackson State 58
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Peter Cipriano's 20 points led four Southern University players in double figures as the Jaguars held on to first place in the Southwestern Athletic Conference with a 70-58 victory over Jackson State on Monday. Southern (10-11, 9-2 SWAC) entered the night tied with Grambling State for first place after losing to the Tigers Saturday night. Southern led Jackson State 18-7 with 13:51 left in the first half but stretched it to 37-24 at the half. Chris Alexander's basket with 14:28 left in the game gave Southern its biggest lead at 50-35. Jackson St. (11-12, 7-4 SWAC) used an 11-2 run to get within 52-46 with 9:30 remaining on a basket from Trey Johnson. But Southern responded with a 6-0 run to push the lead back to 58-46 with 7:19 to play. Alexander added 17 points for Southern, while Jerrid Campbell had 13 and Steffon Wiley contributed 10. Johnson led Jackson State, which shot only 39 percent for the game, with a game high 26 points and Julius Young added 11. Southern outrebounded Jackson State, 42-24.
